page.title: 16WYCH WOOD
page.content: Wych Wood is a private wood lying to the south of Adlington estate.A small brook called Red Brook flows across part of the wood .This area is fairly thickly wooded,the most common tree being oak.Other examples are ash,larch,alder,beech,sycamore,rowan and yew.Beneath the tree cover is bracken and grassland.Bluebells,red campion,cranesbill,bramble and foxgloves were also observed.The wood contains a good deal of wildlife including grey squirrel,fox,rabbit,tawny owl,jay and common garden birds. The soil is mostly leaf mould beneath the trees,but the stream has cut down into the clay subsoil.Around the stream the land is rather swampy. Local people stroll through the wood often taking their dogs for walks.
